<h1 >Guide to Social Security Law Updates - 1993</h1>
<ul><li><a href="15298#16december1993">16 December 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#25november1993">25 November 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#11november1993">11 November 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#21october1993">21 October 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#7october1993">7 October 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#23september1993">23 September 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#2september1993">2 September 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#12august1993">12 August 1993</a></li>
<li><a href="15298#5August1993">5 August 1993</a></li>
</ul><h2 id="16december1993">Update 100G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 23 - ADDITIONAL PAYMENTS -RENT ASSISTANCE, INCENTIVE ALLOWANCE, PHARMACEUTICAL ALLOWANCE, TELEPHONE ALLOWANCE - Rent assistance. See guidelines 23.000 to 23.135.</p>
<p>These references clarify the effect of the three Rent Assistance savings provisions. The first, for certain retirement village residents, provides for the payment of Rent Assistance despite their treatment for other purposes as homeowners. The second, for certain boarders and lodgers, preserves the rules for calculating Rent Assistance that applied at the time. The third, the March 1993 provision, preserves the rate of Rent Assistance they were receiving at the time.</p>
<h2>Update 99G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - New section: Aggregation of primary production assets and liabilities.. See guidelines 27.16030 to 27.16036.</p>
<p>This amendment outlines the background to and the procedures for primary production assets and liabilities under section 1121A of the Act.</p>
<h2>Update 98G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Amendment to table of contents to reflect update 99G. See guidelines 27.16030 to 27.16036.</p>
<h2>Update 97G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 6 - DISABILITY SUPPORT PENSION - Amendment of impairment ratings by social security decision-makers.. See guidelines 6.400 to 6.405.</p>
<p>The change allows social security decision-makers to amend the impairment rating allocated to a client by a Commonwealth Medical Officer without the agreement of AGHS where such an amendment is supported by appropriate medical evidence.</p>
<h2>Update 96G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Effect of cancellation on earnings credit balance. See guidelines 27.17660 to 27.17664.</p>
<p>Amendment states that an earnings credit balance is lost where a pension is cancelled unless the pension is cancelled due to income from employment. In this case, the earnings credit balance must be used up before pension is cancelled.</p>
<h2>Update 95G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - CPI rate changes. See guideline 27.2970.</p>
<p>Updates current and historical rate information.</p>
<h2>Update 94G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - CPI rate changes. See guideline 27.2920.</p>
<p>Updates current and historical rate information.</p>
<h2>Update 93G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - CPI rate changes. See guideline 27.2911.</p>
<p>Updates current and historical rate information.</p>
<h2>Update 92G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - CPI rate changes. See guideline 27.2200.</p>
<p>Updates current and historical rate information.</p>
<h2>Update 91G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - CPI rate changes. See guideline 27.2110.</p>
<p>Updates current and historical rate information.</p>
<h2>Update 90G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - CPI rate changes. See guidelines 27.2020.</p>
<p>Updates current and historical rate information.</p>
<h2>Update 89G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - CPI rate changes. See guidelines 27.2000, 27.2010.</p>
<p>Updates current and historical rate information.</p>
<h2>Update 88G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Life Tables. See guideline 27.13560.</p>
<p>Updates Table of life expectation factors to include 198-87 tables to be used for all pensions/annuities commencing on or after 1 May 1993</p>
<h2>Update 87G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 9 - SOLE PARENT PENSION - Update of NSRS target percentages. See guideline 9.1300.</p>
<p>NSRS target percentages required update upon expiration of National Instruction CB910257.</p>
<h2>Update 86G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Life Tables. See guidelines 27.13720 to 27.13734.</p>
<p>Updates references to Life Expectancy Tables.</p>
<h2>Update 85G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Asylum seeker assistance. See guidelines 1.7800 to 1.7808.</p>
<p>The one week waiting period will now be served concurrently with the 26 week waiting period.</p>
<h2>Update 84G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - 26 week waiting period for newly arrived residents. See guidelines 14.7800 to 12.7803.</p>
<p>The one week waiting period will now be served concurrently with the 26 week waiting period.</p>
<h2>Update 83G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - 26 week waiting period for newly arrived residents. See guidelines 12.7200 to 12.7203.</p>
<p>The one week waiting period will now be served concurrently with the 26 week waiting period.</p>
<h2>Update 82G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - 26 week waiting period for newly arrived residents. See guidelines 12.6200 to 12.6200 (12.6200 deleted).</p>
<p>The one week waiting period will now be served concurrently with the 26 week waiting period.</p>
<h2>Update 81G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Amendment to table of contents to reflect update 82G. See guidelines 12.6100 to 12.6200.</p>
<h2>Update 80G # Date 16 December 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc TAX FILE EXEMPTION NUMBERS - 26 week waiting period for newly arrived residents. See guidelines 1.10500 to 1.10603.</p>
<p>The one week waiting period will now be served concurrently with the 26 week waiting period.</p>
<h2 id="25november1993">Update 79G # Date 25 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 22 - CHILDCARE ASSISTANCE - Child care assistance. See guidelines 22.000 to 22.4101.</p>
<p>Changes to CA assessment procedures and income and assets tests from 1 January 1994.</p>
<h2>Update 78G # Date 25 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Lodgement of claims. See guidelines 1.1400 to 1.1413.</p>
<p>When lodging a claim for additional family payment, this can be treated as a claim for any other social security pension or benefit.</p>
<h2>Update 77G # Date 25 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 6 - DISABILITY SUPPORT PENSION - Amend to incorporate cessation of payment by DSS of TA and LAFHA to clients participating in rehabilitation programs. See guidelines 6.3400 to 6.4109.</p>
<p>Incorporate that fact that DSS no longer administers TA and LAFHA to clients participating in a rehabilitation program.</p>
<h2>Update 76G # Date 25 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 6 - DISABILITY SUPPORT PENSION - Deletion of reference to second medical assessments. See guideline 6.3014.</p>
<p>Remove reference to second medical assessments in line with National Instruction No CB930135.</p>
<h2>Update 75G # Date 25 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - DPS health care card - low income earner. See guideline 27.6300.</p>
<p>New DPS health care card rates of payment.</p>
<h2>Update 74G # Date 25 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 25 - NON-CASH BENEFITS - Health care cards. See guideline 25.4300.</p>
<p>Addition to five groups of disadvantaged clients.</p>
<h2 id="11november1993">Update 73G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 25 - NON-CASH BENEFITS - 1. Date of effect of savings provision for HCC. See guidelines 25.7400 to 25.7407.</p>
<p>Amending incorrect date of effect of savings provision.</p>
<h2>Update 72G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - 1. Taxable income of new arrivals in Australia (see guidelines 27.25400 to 27.25401) 2. Taxable income of defence force personnel stationed overseas (see guidelines 27.25500 to 27.25501).</p>
<p>1. With the inclusion of foreign income in the Family Payment income test, new arrivals in Australia will be assessed on their taxable income plus any foreign income.</p>
<p>2. Changes to the way in which foreign income is assessed in the Family Payment income test may have implications for defence force personnel stationed overseas.</p>
<h2>Update 71G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Foreign income. See guidelines 27.25050 to 27.25153.</p>
<p>Foreign income will be included in the Family Payment income test.</p>
<h2>Update 70G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Amendment to table of contents to reflect update 71G.</p>
<h2>Update 69G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Casual earnings and the income test. See guidelines 27.8610 to 27.8619.</p>
<p>This amendment provides examples, calculating the income amounts for casual employees such as school teachers and TAFE lecturers.</p>
<h2>Update 68G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - The 'youth summit' resulted in changes to the education leavers waiting period, effective from 2 November 1992. These changes included a change for secondary education leavers. The education leavers waiting period for these people now starts from the day after a person leaves a full time course of education and ends no later than 14 February. See guidelines 12.6700 to 12.6702.</p>
<p>Update example for secondary education leavers.</p>
<h2>Update 67G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 18 - CHILD DISABILITY ALLOWANCE - Dual claims for family payment ane CDA. See guideline 18.100 to 18.103.</p>
<p>Family payment is income tested for CDA children.</p>
<h2>Update 66G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 6 - DISABILITY SUPPORT PENSION - Removal of reference to second medical assessments. See guidelines 6.400 to 6.405.</p>
<p>Guideline 6.402 currently refers to the policy of offering second medical assessments where a client receives an initial impairment rating of less than 20%. This policy was abolished from 26 July 1993 and the second dot point in 6.402 should therefore be removed.</p>
<h2>Update 65G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Additional earnings free area. See guidelines 27.7210 to 27.7227.</p>
<p>Pensioners granted war widow's pension with effect from 1 November 1986 are paid with a ceiling of $120.10. People paid an allowance or benefit who are granted a war widow's pension with effect from 1 November 1986 become ineligible for payment of allowance or benefit.</p>
<h2>Update 64G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 6 - DISABILITY SUPPORT PENSION - Manifest inability to work. See guidelines 6.1010 to 6.1032.</p>
<p>The 'manifest medical conditions' have been re-structured.</p>
<h2>Update 63G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 6 - DISABILITY SUPPORT PENSION - Definition of work skill levels. See guidelines 6.740 to 6.763.</p>
<p>This amendment replaces the definition of work as 'unskilled', 'semi-skilled' and 'skilled' with three categories of work defined according to the level of formal education, training or work experience required to perform the work.</p>
<h2>Update 62G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Waiving education leaver waiting periods. See guidelines 12.6850 to 12.6853.</p>
<p>Clarifies the position when a person reclaims JSA within 12 months of commencing a course of study after having served a partial ELWP.</p>
<h2>Update 61G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Education leaver waiting periods. Guidelines 12.6600 to 12.6603 deleted.</p>
<h2>Update 60G # Date 11 November 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12- NEWSTART - Amendment to Table of Contents to reflect update 61G.</p>
<h2 id="21october1993">Update 59G # Date 21 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Certain 15 years may qualify for special benefit if they don't satisfy all eligibility criteria for job search or sickness allowance. See guidelines 15.2830 to 15.2832.</p>
<p>Certain 15 year olds quality for job search and sickness allowance if they reach the minimum school leaving age, not living with or supported by parents, and there full-time employment history or registered by unemployed for periods adding up to 13 weeks. If a client is not registered for periods adding up to 13 weeks, they may still qualify for special benefit if exempt from the parental means test (1067-C2).</p>
<h2>Update 58G # Date 21 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Earned income free area. See guideline 27.5200.</p>
<p>The 'Investing in the Nation' statement (February 1993) announced from 20 September 1993 an introduction of an earnings free area of $30.00 pf for single people and an increase from $30.00 to $50.00 pf. in the earnings free area for each member of a couple. Changes to the earned income free area will assist in increasing the number of clients and their partners gaining employment providing a basis for a transition to full-time employment. It provides a financial incentive for employment and directs the benefits of income test liberalisation away from those with substantial income from investments.</p>
<h2>Update 57G # Date 21 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Approved care organisations. See guidelines 17.2420 to 17.2510.</p>
<p>An ACO is eligible for family payment when; a) the person is a young person, b) the young person is an inhabitant of Australia, c) the person is a client of the ACO and d) no person is receiving family payment for the young person.</p>
<h2>Update 56G # Date 21 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES INC. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Available funds test to be applied to PRC Nationals. See guidelines 1.7930 to 1.7939.</p>
<p>Removes the general provision that the short term available funds test is applicable to all special benefit cases paid under JSA conditions.</p>
<h2 id="7october1993">Update 55G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Review of support provided by third parties. See guidelines 15.4000 to 15.4004.</p>
<p>Highlights the need to consider changes in circumstances of relevant third parties.</p>
<h2>Update 54G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Cessation of payments to a care organisation. See guidelines 17.5600 to 17.5604.</p>
<p>Where the provisions in section A:5 about dependent children are satisfied, the payment may be considered to have been suspended for that child.</p>
<h2>Update 53G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 4 - NEGLIGENCE CLAIMS, ACT OF GRACE PAYMENTS - Application of Finance Direction 21/3 where a right to internal review exists under the Act. See guidelines 4.1300 to 4.6004.</p>
<p>New text explains that where the Act provides for a right of review of a decision, there will not generally be a common law duty of care attached to the decision. This means that the Department should generally deny liability where an incorrect decision is made under the Act that is adverse to the client or does not provide the client with their full entitlement, where the client had a right to internal review under the Act.</p>
<h2>Update 52G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Rate payable to a dependent partner of a person imprisoned or on remand. See guidelines 15.3600 to 15.3604.</p>
<p>Rate payable to a dependent partner of a person imprisoned or on remand has changed from half married rate to single rate.</p>
<h2>Update 51G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Rate of benefit payable. See guidelines 15.1800 to 15.1805.</p>
<p>Provides details of the rate of benefit payable where the partner does not qualify for a payment or does not attract additional payment, or where other support is provided.</p>
<h2>Update 50G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Direct deduction income test. See guidelines 15.1100 to 15.1102.</p>
<p>Where a partner does not qualify for a payment in their own right or they are unable to attract additional payment, only half of the combined income is to be maintained as a direct deduction.</p>
<h2>Update 49G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Duration of common categories. See guideline 15.810.</p>
<p>Guide to which categories of special benefit are generally treated as short or long term</p>
<h2>Update 48G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 19 - DOUBLE ORPHAN PENSION - Double dipping provisions for double orphan pension. See guidelines 19.110 to 19.112.</p>
<p>Double orphan pension not payable to clients, where the child receives income over the permissable earnings, including AUSTUDY.</p>
<h2>Update 47G # Date 7 October 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 19 - DOUBLE ORPHAN PENSION - Amendment to table of contents to reflect update 48G.</p>
<h2 id="23september1993">Update 46G # Date 23 September 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Notification requirements for continuing payments. See guidelines 17.3000 to 17.3002.</p>
<p>Changes to BFP and AFP assets thresholds and rate of permissable student earnings.</p>
<h2>Update 45G # Date 23 September 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Payment of arrears. See guidelines 17.300 to 17.301.</p>
<p>The sixth situation where FP arrears are payable is when a client applies for family payment after a child AUSTUDY claim is rejected and a copy of the rejection letter is produced within 28 days.</p>
<h2>Update 44G # Date 23 September 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES - Released prisoners (new Part K). See guidelines 1.17000 to 1.20600.</p>
<p>Outlines available options when claimants are released prisoners. Emphasises that eligibility for all other payment types must be investigated before the payment of special benefit can be considered.</p>
<h2>Update 43G # Date 23 September 1993</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES - Released prisoners (new Part K). See guidelines 1.12000 to 1.16300.</p>
<p>Outlines available options when claimants are released prisoners. Emphasises that eligibility for all other payment types must be investigated before the payment of special benefit can be considered.</p>
<h2>Update 42G # Date 23 September 1993</h2>
